<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-11-04T10:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-11-04T10:00:00-05:00" n="629" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d629">
                                <note rend="inline" type="source">123 P 54/524: Telegram</note>
                                <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi>
                                        (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Winant</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                                <opener>
                                    <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-11-04T16:00:00+01:00">November 4, 1942—4
                                            p.m.</date><lb/>[Received November 4—3:40
                                        p.m.]</dateline>
                                </opener>
                                <p>6173. Personal for the Secretary from William Phillips. Your
                                    5487, November 3, 7 p.m. I deeply appreciate the confidence
                                    which the President and you place in me in asking me to
                                    undertake this important mission. Please assure the President
                                    that I will do my utmost to carry out his purposes and that I am
                                    ready to proceed to New Delhi whenever it is thought advisable.
                                    I look forward with enthusiasm to the task. [Phillips.]</p>
                                <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Winant</hi></signed></closer>
                            </div>
                            </body></text></TEI>